{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":33934,"name":"","username":"Avagrande","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/avagrande/{size}/2686_2.png","created_at":"2019-09-21T10:13:08.681Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI am working on animated transitions between two different states of a render surface.\u003cbr\u003e\nBut to accomplish this I have to create a image for the current and next state so I can render their stills together during the animation.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe way I accomplish this is by fetching the image from the texture bound to my render surface and copying it into a new texture. However I cannot update a canvas without rendering it to the screen so the users sees a brief flash of the next frame before the transition begins as I use \u003ccode\u003eGetEngine():RunFrame()\u003c/code\u003e to force a render target to be filled with the next state.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis works as intended although with undesirable Update event which is unnecessary and in some cases it causes a flash of the frame I never want the user to see.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIs there a way I can update a singular render surface without causing a global update? I only want this one updated.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-09-21T10:13:08.681Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":6,"reads":30,"readers_count":29,"score":51.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":5609,"topic_slug":"off-screen-render-surface-updates-without-global-update","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1201,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":33945,"name":"SirNate0","username":"SirNate0","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/9f8e36/{size}.png","created_at":"2019-09-21T13:34:57.281Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eYou should be able to render to a texture instead of the screen‚Äôs render target. I believe there‚Äôs a couple threads with code to set such a thing up, as well as an example in the samples. It kind of sounds like you may already be doing this, so if that‚Äôs the case sorry for not being able to help.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-09-21T13:34:57.281Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":27,"readers_count":26,"score":5.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":5609,"topic_slug":"off-screen-render-surface-updates-without-global-update","display_username":"SirNate0","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":628,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":33949,"name":"","username":"Bananaft","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/bananaft/{size}/222_2.png","created_at":"2019-09-21T16:59:24.758Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eDo you want a cross-fade transition effect between two shots, right?\u003cbr\u003e\nI feel like it should be done entirely on GPU by switching renderpath commands.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou can make a post-effect that draws old copied frame on top of current render result and then slowly fade it out.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"po